This paper is primarily focused on the design of physical and medium access control layers of wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also discusses issues related to synchronization and error-control coding, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of wireless social networks and emergency situations, which could be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SY), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses security issues related to error-control coding, which could be classified under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
